Ron:
 
From here it didn't sound like Ed Foster was denying that all the shit
and glory of our daily lives--even the political shit and
glory--belongs in our poems.
 
I thought his point had more to do with the difference between, say,
_The Communist Manifesto_ and _A_. Not that I don't enjoy _The
Communist Manifesto_--I like happy endings as much as the next guy,
but I try not to confuse them with poetry.
 
Mike
mboughn@epas.utoronto.ca
