From:         Andrew Joron <ajoron@EMF.NET>
Subject:      reductionism
 
Poetry may contain or be conditioned by numerous factors like
politics, sexuality, nationality, etc. but what "saves" any
given poem *as a poem* is not reducible to any one factor,
or ensemble of factors. The argument becomes one against
reductionism.
                   Andrew Joron
