Stephen Cope mentioned that while O'Hara is a "homosexual" poet,
Creeley is just a poet. I dunno. I know people who thibnk of Creeley
as an American poet. I myself always think of him as a one-eyed poet.
 
But seriously, I do remember that about 20 years ago Ginsberg
descriobed my and Victor Coleman as good heterosexual poets. As it
was the first time anyone had called me that I was a little tripped,
and then I liked it. But I havent, I think, been called that by a
hetero-breeder poet, that I know of.
 
Still, I have heard O'Hara called a NY poet 200 times for every time
I have heard him called a gay poet. And Jack? Well, Jack is Jack. I
hold his imaginary hand.
