From:         cris cheek <cris@SLANG.DEMON.CO.UK>
Subject:      Re: politics
X-cc:         Michael Boughn <mboughn@epas.utoronto.ca>
 
The first translation of 'The Communist Manifesto' into English was by
Helen Macfarlane and published in George Julian Harney's 'The Red
Republican' on Saturday, November 9, 1850. [Price One Penny]
 
Translation buffs will be amused to know that she sandbaggeded its famous
opening line from the plain and direct 'A Spectre is haunting Europe' to 'A
frightful hobgoblin stalks throughout Europe'.
 
Resultant mutual suspicions between revolution and poetry have been a
struggle ever since.
 
game on
cris
