From:         Ron Silliman <rsillima@IX.NETCOM.COM>
Subject:      Re: jazz/poetry
 
In the late 1970s, I had a rare demo record of a session Lorenzo Thomas
did fronting a blues/rock band while in college (Queens? Brooklyn?).
The band was called The Bankers -- hard to imagine that image for
Lorenzo -- and he wrote the lyrics, sang the songs. I remember one
verse: "bedbug morning, silverfish afternoon."
 
The acoustics were dreadful but the music was out there. I got the
record from the bass player (Rich Jenkins, the younger brother of the
playwright Len whom Douglas has published on more than one occasion). I
gave my copy back to Lorenzo when I learned that he had lost the only
copy he had had.
 
My question: are there any other recordings of him w/ musicians out
there?
