Sender:       UB Poetics discussion group <POETICS@UBVM.CC.BUFFALO.EDU>
From:         braman sandra <s-braman@UX1.CSO.UIUC.EDU>
Subject:      net dissemination
 
Speaking of dissemination -- a couple of guys are about to start up a
book distribution service for fiction.  You pay a nominal fee to put in
your manuscript.  Readers can read a few pages before making a decision
to order it, at which paying for the book with a computerized transaction
delivers the entire manuscript.  Authors get a royalty of a few dollars
apiece.  Sounds great, frankly.  Why only fiction?
Needs a server, some software, someone to put in a little time running it.
Sandra Braman
 
PS -- If anyone's interested in putting a manuscript up for the fiction
server, please let me know backchannel (s-braman@ux1.cso.uiuc.edu), and
I'll pass your names along.
