Date:         Thu, 27 Apr 1995 10:47:00 -0400
Reply-To:     UB Poetics discussion group <POETICS@UBVM.CC.BUFFALO.EDU>
Sender:       UB Poetics discussion group <POETICS@UBVM.CC.BUFFALO.EDU>
From:         Tom Mandel <tmandel@UMD5.UMD.EDU>
Subject:      Re: Re Mandel/Mao
 
My error, Herb, and thanks for pointing it out, in the Sabbatean
antinomian blessing, which should read:
 
        Blessed be the Lord our God, King of the universe,
        who permitteth that which is forbidden.
 
It might also be translated "which permitteth" as the rabbis
tried to avoid formulations that would anthropomorphize God,
often inserting the phrase "as it were" where the language led
them to such forms -- this despite God's showing Moses his
ass in the desert.
 
Tom Mandel
