Just to echo Ron's excitement at receiving the Leave pamphlets in the
mail. I received these last week as well, and they are marvelous. Thanks,
Juliana. As to the micropress, stitched pamphlets in SPD or other
bookstores, I wish there were more everywhere, but I even think that, in
the context of most bookstores they are rather lost, whereas they are so
convenient and not terribly expensive, to mail. Getting them in the mail
is a wonder rarely found in a bookstore. Perhaps, then, there is simply a
need for more access to finding out about such works so that more people
can order them or trade for them. I think this list and other electronic
forums are already helping in that regard.
 
